          <p>
          </p>
          <span style="font-family: tahoma; font-size: 18px;">
           <p>
            Heaton Park Tramway is run by the Manchester Transport Museum Society. We have a variety of electric trams some in store and others operational and running on a stretch of track dating back to the original Manchester Tramway which used to operate into the park. Since opening in 1980, we have extended the line three times and run from Middleton Road to the boating lake.
           </p>
           <p>
            Why not come &amp; visit we would love to meet you.
           </p>
           <p>
            <strong>
             Our tramway is currently open every Saturday, Sunday &amp; Bank Holiday Monday, as well as Wednesdays until the end of August!
            </strong>
           </p>
           <p>
            <strong>
             Trams will run from 12pm until 5pm-ish, subject to demand.
             <br/>
            </strong>
           </p>

           <span id="ctl00_phContent_lblSessionTime">

           <input class="btnSession" id="ctl00_phContent_btnSession" name="ctl00$phContent$btnSession" onclick="ResetSessionLabel();" type="submit" value="Click here to continue working"/>
          </div>
         </div>
         <script type="text/javascript">
          var sessionTimeout = parseInt("60");
             var _sessionTimer;
             function DisplaySessionTimeout() {
                 //assigning minutes left to session timeout to Label
                 $("#ctl00_phContent_lblSessionTime").html(sessionTimeout);
                 
                 sessionTimeout = sessionTimeout - 1;
 
                 //if session is not less than 0
                 if (sessionTimeout > 0) {
                     if (sessionTimeout <= 5) {
                         $(".sessionTime").show();
                         if (sessionTimeout == 1)
                             $("#ctl00_phContent_lblSessionTime").html("Your session will end in less than a minute.");
                         else
                             $("#ctl00_phContent_lblSessionTime").html("Your session will end in " + sessionTimeout + " minutes.");
                     }
                     else {
                         $(".sessionTime").hide();
                     }
                     _sessionTimer = window.setTimeout("DisplaySessionTimeout()", 60000);
                 }
                 else {
                     $(".sessionTime").show();
                     $("#ctl00_phContent_lblSessionTime").html("Your session has ended.");
                 }
             }
 
             function ResetSessionLabel() {
                 sessionTimeout = parseInt("60");
                 $(".sessionTime").hide();
                 window.clearTimeout(_sessionTimer);
                 _sessionTimer = window.setTimeout("DisplaySessionTimeout()", 60000);// 60000);
             }
         </script>
